        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "There is a notice about an undeclared \"length\" in the describeTable() method (with pdo_pgsql)\n\nif ($val['type'] === 'varchar') {\n                \/\/ need to add length to the type so we are compatible with\n                \/\/ Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Pgsql!\n                $val['type'] .= '(' . $val['length']  . ')';\n}\n\n\nThe 'length' index is not declared in the SQL query :\n\n$sql = \"SELECT a.atttypmod AS length, a.attnum, a.attname AS field, t.typname AS type, \"\n             . \"a.attnotnull AS isnotnull, \"\n             . \"( SELECT 't' \"\n             . \"FROM pg_index \"\n             . \"WHERE c.oid = pg_index.indrelid \"\n             . \"AND pg_index.indkey[0] = a.attnum \"\n             . \"AND pg_index.indisprimary = 't') AS pri, \"\n             . \"(SELECT pg_attrdef.adsrc \"\n             . \"FROM pg_attrdef \"\n             . \"WHERE c.oid = pg_attrdef.adrelid \"\n             . \"AND pg_attrdef.adnum=a.attnum) AS default \"\n             . \"FROM pg_attribute a, pg_class c, pg_type t \"\n             . \"WHERE c.relname = '{$table}' \"\n             . \"AND a.attnum > 0 \"\n             . \"AND a.attrelid = c.oid \"\n             . \"AND a.atttypid = t.oid \"\n             . \"ORDER BY a.attnum \";\n\n\nThe solution is probably to add :\n\n\"a.atttypmod AS length\"\n\nin the SQL query\n\nbut the atttypemod field seems to be the searched length + 4. So I use :\n\n($val['length'] - 4)"
        },
